HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 99
BY REPRESENTATIVE KERNER
CRIMINAL/JUSTICE: Creates the Louisiana Electronic Monitoring and GPS Oversight
Task Force
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To create the Louisiana Electronic Monitoring and Global Positioning System Oversight
3 Task Force to study and make recommendations relative to statewide oversight,
4 infrastructure, reporting, accountability, investigative duties, provider duties, and
5 public safety standards for electronic monitoring and global positioning system
6 (GPS) monitoring in Louisiana.
7 WHEREAS, electronic monitoring and GPS monitoring are increasingly used
8 throughout Louisiana as conditions of pretrial release, probation, parole, home incarceration,
9 protective orders, domestic violence supervision, victim-safety conditions, and other
10 court-ordered or agency-ordered supervision; and
11 WHEREAS, electronic monitoring and GPS monitoring are no longer merely private
12 services between providers and individuals, but a public safety function that affects courts,
13 prosecutors, law enforcement, victims, supervised individuals, providers, and the public; and
14 WHEREAS, Louisiana has a strong public safety interest in ensuring that electronic
15 monitoring and GPS monitoring are conducted with clear standards, reliable infrastructure,
16 timely reporting, transparent accountability, and consistent statewide oversight; and
17 WHEREAS, the effectiveness of electronic monitoring and GPS monitoring depends
18 not only on the device placed on an individual, but also on the oversight system surrounding
19 that device, including the ordering authority, the individual being monitored, the entity
20 responsible for monitoring, the applicable conditions, the recipients of violation reports, and
21 the actions taken in response to a violation; and
